                {
                    "name": "Bar Brawler",
                    "type": "stat_block_section",
                    "text": "The barkeep has been in enough bar fights to know how to throw a few punches. When fighting in their bar and making a <a aonid=\"188\" game-obj=\"Traits\">nonlethal</a> attack, the barkeep gains a +1 circumstance bonus to attack rolls and deals an additional 1d4 damage.",
                    "subtype": "offensive_action"
                },
                {
                    "name": "Barkeep's Advice",
                    "type": "stat_block_section",
                    "text": "<b>Frequency</b> once per day; <b>Effect</b> The barkeep gives some pertinent advice to a single creature other than themself. For 24 hours, when that creature fails a skill check or saving throw, they can recall this advice and reroll the check, using the second result instead. Once that creature uses this ability, its effect ends. A creature that receives the Barkeep's Advice is temporarily immune to the ability for 1 month.",
                    "subtype": "offensive_action",
